  "text": "Flat epithelial atypia was defined as dilated acini lined by up to a few layers of cells with round to oval nuclei and apical snouts. [CITATION_1] The nuclei were typically small and evenly spaced. Occasionally the nuclei were larger with more obvious atypia. Atypical ductal hyperplasia is a diagnosis that strictly should be reserved for surgical specimens. Nevertheless, we used this term for proliferations of cells with small evenly spaced nuclei with solid, cribriform or micropapillary architecture. An important criterion was that low grade DCIS was being considered, but the changes were not sufficient for this diagnosis.",
